Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine orange-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Agelochos. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0035.33.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0395)
